Years of poor oyster harvests have waterman Bill Beck worried about the future of the industry for his son.
Recently, the Beck family, spanning three generations, set out to harvest nearly 4,000 bushels of disease-free oysters from managed reserves.
Environmentalists are frustrated with the slow progress in cleaning up the Chesapeake Bay, leading to legal action against the EPA.
Nutria, causing economic damage, are being targeted for removal in Maryland.
Efforts to restore the bay include introducing Asian oysters, but concerns about their impact on the ecosystem persist.
Despite challenges, traditional oyster festivals continue to celebrate the bay's heritage.
